mansa11
Can anyone please explain how the calls to the connectors from the accountingManager works?
stakog 05/03/2024 20:07
When executeDeposit is called, funds (base token) are moved from accountingManager to a connector contract via the connector's addLiquidity function. For the opposite direction, when the accountingManager needs funds for withdrawal requests, it has the function retrieveTokensForWithdraw to retrieve the base token from the connectors. Note that the connectors should already hold the funds. There is another flow for depositing and retrieving funds between connectors and external protocols (i.e. positions). This is how I understand the mechanics. (edited)
2

So I'll explain the idea with an example: In uniswap connector, the goal is to deposit tokens into the uniswap pool and hold the position NFT For doing so, we need to add its corresponding "trustedPositionBP" to the registery so the registry acknowledges this position as a valid position in this vault Then later when we actually create that position, the connector contract creates a Holding position in the registry which represents the position NFT To explain in simple words: trustedPositionBP are the potential positions and Holding positions are the positions that we actually have at the moment
